</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="293" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,259,1222]" pageId="4" pageNumber="293">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1159,1185]" pageId="4" pageNumber="293">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named in honour of the Lithuanian entomologist Aidas Saldaitis (
<collectingRegion box="[1225,1310,1159,1185]" country="Lithuania" name="Vilniaus" pageId="4" pageNumber="293">Vilnius</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1320,1429,1159,1186]" name="Lithuania" pageId="4" pageNumber="293">Lithuania</collectingCountry>
) who collected many Chinese moths.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
